Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You may watch the recording above. CAPE TOWN - Opposition parties have called on all South Africans to march on the day of a motion of no confidence in President Jacob Zuma. The parties want a vote on the motion this week. The leaders of opposition parties in Parliament briefed the media following a meeting held on Monday to discuss a number of "pressing" issues of "national importance". The opposition parties are calling on President Jacob Zuma to step down. The EFF had written to Speaker of Parliament Baleka Mbete requesting a motion of no confidence in Zuma to be debated on Tuesday. Mbete has scheduled the motion to be debated on 22 February. eNCA